  "body": "# Bug Report\r\n\r\n## Description\r\n\r\nIt's not purely  a bug, but it's not really  a feature either. It's basically that it's bad UX right now in the Create Community Popup.\r\nWhen you enter a Name and Description, the Next button is still disabled.\r\n\r\nWe should make it clear which fields are necessary.\r\n\r\nI'll leave it up to the design and UI team to decide what is the best way. Propositions:\r\n- Add an asterisk `*` next to the obligatory field\r\n- Add text somewhere of the missing fields that gets updated when a field is filled\r\n- Add a tooltip on the button saying which fields are missing\r\n- Let the button be enabled, but clicking it shows an \"error\" state on the mssing states\r\n\r\n## Steps to reproduce\r\n\r\n0. Be in release (or set `isDevBuild` to `false` in `CreateCommunityPopup.qml`)\r\n1. Go to the portal\r\n2. Hit Create New Community\r\n3. Hit Create New\r\n4. Enter Name and Description\r\n5. Button is still disabled and we don't know why\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n",
